<lb/><p>My dear<persName> M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi>Napier</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I thank you 
<lb/>very much for kindly 
<lb/>remembering me 
<lb/>in the Launch and 
<lb/>trial trip. I shall 
<lb/>be unable to avail 
<lb/>myself the pleasure 
<lb/>of seeing the launch 
<lb/>but I should like 
<lb/><!-- TODO SM: Is this an addSpan? If so, it needs to be coded as such. written along left hand side of first page - MH -->mention only to friends who can 
<w>appre-<lb break="no"/>ciate</w> them. I am your 
<lb/><persName>David Livingstone</persName>

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002349_0002"/><!--pb/@n='1v'-->
<lb/>the last duty<reg>.</reg> o her yesterday 
<lb/>Tell <persName>M<hi rend="underline">rs</hi> Napier</persName>that the 
<lb/>great change appeared only 
<lb/>an hour before the dose 
<lb/>in quicker breathing. My 
<lb/><persName>sister</persName> said. "I think the 
<lb/>Saviour has come 
<lb/>for your mother. You 
<lb/>can lippon yourself to 
<lb/>him." "Oh yes she said 
<lb/>in a way that only we 
<lb/>Scotch can understand 
<lb/>gave a last look to our 
<lb/>little girl &amp; send " bonnie 
<lb/>wee lassie" closed her 
<lb/>eyes &amp; soon all was still. We are thankful 
<lb/>to believe that she is safe 
<lb/>in the haven of mercy 
<lb/>These little things we </p>
			
